&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name>Tao He</name></author><category term="Jekyll" /><summary type="html">A wide tables needs to be wrapped into a div with class table-wrapper to make sure it displayed as expected on mobile devices. For example,</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Page with cover image</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/2022-05-24-page_cover.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Page with cover image" /><published>2022-05-24T00:00:00+03:00</published><updated>2022-05-24T00:00:00+03:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/page_cover</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/2022-05-24-page_cover.html">&lt;p&gt;The jekyll-gitbook theme supports adding a cover image to a specific page by adding
a &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;cover&lt;/code&gt; field to the page metadata:&lt;/p&gt;

