&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name>Tao He</name></author><category term="Jekyll" /><summary type="html">The jekyll-gitbook theme supports adding a cover image to a specific page by adding a cover field to the page metadata:</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">How to Generate TOC</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/2021-08-10-toc.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to Generate TOC" /><published>2021-08-10T00:00:00+03:00</published><updated>2021-08-10T00:00:00+03:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/toc</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/jekyll-gitbook/jekyll/2021-08-10-toc.html">&lt;p&gt;The jekyll-gitbook theme leverages &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/allejo/jekyll-toc&quot;&gt;jekyll-toc&lt;/a&gt; to generate the &lt;em&gt;Contents&lt;/em&gt; for the page.
